This documentation describes the Pivotal Developer Console (PDC). The Pivotal Developer Console enables platform teams to curate a set of brokered services for use by application teams across many platforms (such as Kubernetes and PAS.)

## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

PDC allows platform teams to curate and register Open Service Broker API (OSBAPI) compliant service brokers, which can be running anywhere as long as they are accessible by PDC, to a single centralised location.

These brokers can then be used by application teams to provision services and retrieve credentials, via the `pdc` command line tool. Their applications, which could be living across multiple platforms, can then use these credentials to access the service instances.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

<%= vars.product_full %> includes the following key features:

* Register OSBAPI compliant brokers
* Create and access services on applications running across multiple platforms
* Have a docker image registry that images can be relocated to.

